ce:section.ce:para:
The fluorescent detection strategies of curcumin are closely related with its optical properties. Curcumin, 1,7-bis-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)-1,6-heptadiene- 2,5-dione (Fig. 1
                     ) [21], does not well dissolve in water, but is easily dispersed in ethanol. The color of curcumin in the ethanol solution appears yellow with a maximum absorption peak at 420 nm in the ultraviolet–visible (UV–vis) absorption spectrum. And the solution is observed to display yellow-green fluorescence under UV light. The emission spectra of curcumin exhibit a excitation-independent emission behavior with a maximum fluorescence emission peak centered at 525 nm (Fig. 2
                     ) [22]. Based on these optical properties of curcumin, various fluorescent nanosensors have been constructed.
